{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"duration_ms":75000,"duration_api_ms":74844,"num_turns":8,"result":"Here's a summary of the findings:\n\n## Root Cause\n\n**File:** `src/requests/sessions.py`, `SessionRedirectMixin.rebuild_proxies()`, lines 318-319 and 328.\n\nThe logic:\n1. **Line 318-319** — `Proxy-Authorization` is **unconditionally deleted** from the headers whenever `rebuild_proxies()` is called.\n2. **Line 328** — It is only **re-added** if `not scheme.startswith(\"https\") and username and password` — meaning it is never restored for HTTPS requests.\n\n```python\nif \"Proxy-Authorization\" in headers:\n    del headers[\"Proxy-Authorization\"]          # always stripped\n\n# only restored for HTTP, never HTTPS:\nif not scheme.startswith(\"https\") and username and password:\n    headers[\"Proxy-Authorization\"] = _basic_auth_str(username, password)\n```\n\n## Why It Happens\n\nThis was intentional for HTTPS targets: urllib3 handles proxy auth internally via `HTTPAdapter.proxy_headers()` during the CONNECT tunnel. Injecting `Proxy-Authorization` manually into the tunnelled request would leak credentials to the destination server, not the proxy. So requests strips it.\n\n## Fix for the User\n\nEmbed credentials in the proxy URL instead of setting the header manually:\n```python\nrequests.get(\"https://example.com\", proxies={\"https\": \"http://user:pass@proxy:8080\"})\n```\n\nThe answer has been written to `/workspace/agent_output/answer.json`.","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"36ff5aa1-70e3-4d8b-b853-8ccf0b676df8","total_cost_usd":0.1944078,"usage":{"input_tokens":10,"cache_creation_input_tokens":15084,"cache_read_input_tokens":113387,"output_tokens":2365,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":15084},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"},"modelUsage":{"claude-sonnet-4-6":{"inputTokens":10,